The league has been calling for the ANC MP to resign and threatening that it will picket outside her house and every event she attends JOHANNESBURG - African National Congress (ANC) MP Makhosi Khoza says she fears for her life after receiving several threats from the ANC Youth League (ANCYL) in KwaZulu-Natal (KZN).Khoza says the threats came after a Facebook post where she stated that one s moral conscience cannot be divorced from their political choices and decisions.The league has been calling for Khoza to resign and threatening that it will picket outside her house and every event she attends.Khoza says she also fears for the safety of her children. Can we please strengthen this democracy. Let s not resort to violence when we disagree with our fellow south Africans or comrades. We need to grow. I can t be subjected to the same conditions as I went through in the 1980s during apartheid days in KZN when we had so much violence and my house was burnt down. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)